# WhisperLog Environment Variables Template
# ============================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual credentials
# DO NOT commit .env - it contains sensitive information
# .env is in .gitignore and will not be tracked by git

# Gemini API Key
# Get from: https://aistudio.google.com/
# Used for: AI note classification and intelligent processing
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# Google OAuth 2.0 Web Client ID
# Get from: Google Cloud Console -> APIs & Services -> Credentials
# Used for: Google Sign-In on web platform
GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID=your_google_web_client_id_here

# Telegram Bot Username (Optional)
# Only needed if implementing Telegram integration
# Format: @your_bot_username
TELEGRAM_BOT_USERNAME=your_telegram_bot_username

# Firebase Configuration Files (NOT in this file)
# ===============================================
# These are binary/JSON files that are also in .gitignore:
#
# Android:
#   - Place google-services.json in: android/app/google-services.json
#   - Get from: Firebase Console -> Project Settings -> Download google-services.json
#
# iOS:
#   - Place GoogleService-Info.plist in: ios/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist
#   - Get from: Firebase Console -> Project Settings -> Download GoogleService-Info.plist
#
# Generated (DO NOT edit, auto-generated):
#   - lib/firebase_options.dart (generated by FlutterFire CLI)
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Get google-services.json from Firebase Console
# 2. Open it to verify it contains your project ID: "wishperlog"
# 3. Place it in android/app/ directory
# 4. git status should NOT show these files (they're in .gitignore)

# Security Notes
# ==============
# - Never commit .env file to git
# - Never commit google-services.json to git
# - Never commit GoogleService-Info.plist to git
# - All these files are listed in .gitignore
# - If exposed, regenerate all API keys immediately
